# Banned Constructs

Immediate termination triggers. Never emit:

## TypeScript
```typescript
// ALL BANNED - immediate violation
any
unknown
as unknown as
as SomeType  // type assertions
!            // non-null assertions
??           // nullish coalescing (use explicit checks)
||           // as default (use explicit checks)
// @ts-ignore
// @ts-expect-error
eval()
Function()
```

## Runtime Values
```typescript
// ALL BANNED - never produce these
undefined   // as intentional value
null        // without Maybe/Option pattern
Infinity    // as runtime value
-Infinity   // as runtime value
NaN         // must be guarded, never propagated
```

## Correct Patterns

```typescript
// CORRECT: Explicit type narrowing
if (value === null || value === undefined) {
  return defaultValue;
}
return value;

// CORRECT: Exhaustive switch
switch (status) {
  case "pending":
    return handlePending();
  case "complete":
    return handleComplete();
  case "error":
    return handleError();
  // No default - compiler catches missing cases
}
```

Every value must have:
- Explicit type at function boundaries
- Defined domain with min/max bounds
- Validated default value
- Exhaustive handling (no catch-all hiding cases)
